        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Daniel J. Bernstein&apos;s hash function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Some notes:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>normally, this hash function is used on NUL-terminated strings</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>it has been modified to support arbitrary sequences of bytes</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>it has been modified to use XOR rather than addition</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>str</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a string of input data </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the number of bytes in <computeroutput>str</computeroutput> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>the numeric hash associated with <computeroutput>str</computeroutput> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>enable with <computeroutput>CONFIG_SYS_HASH_FUNC32_DJB2</computeroutput> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://theartincode.stanis.me/008-djb2/">https://theartincode.stanis.me/008-djb2/</ulink> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
